Acne can be very complicated sometimes. 
You can do all the steps necessary, layer the right products, and the best BUT you may still get a breakout the next morning. 
Reasons maybe cause if hormones, bad eating habits, touching your face, or anything else. 

And it’s all good and normal. 

Also it doesn’t mean you have to give up on your routine and skincare. 
Sudden surprises like this can be taken care of 💗

✨Special Credit✨

 Thank you to my friends for being a part of my reels💗
#skincare #pimple #acne #skincareroutine

My acne and PIH journey was long and tbh very discouraging. Until I added this product into my routine. 

The @isntree Onion NewPair Gel cream will forever be on my top list. 

As someone who didn’t not have acne until I was 23, mostly cause of pore diet, habits and stress. Adult acne really caught on well, but that was also the reason how I got into K-Beauty which transformed my skin. 
But fast forward to 2020, another acne breakout season begun, it was due to hormonal imbalance, again stress. Around that time we were all going through a lot a once but it’s also around then my love for skincare, mostly K-Beauty blossomed again and I tried so many products which worked and did not as well. 

But this was also the time my skin was going through a massive change and when I gave a really deep thought on what knowing my skin meant. 
Going deeper into understanding my skin, listening to its needs and actually walking along side the demands & requirement of my skin led me to today’s skin. 

And i’m glad that’s I got to be apart of @beautybarnindia at the same time. Being able to experience such, opened a whole new world where I help share & spread the awareness about listening to your skin’s needs. 

I’ll share the products that changed my skin in the next reels.
